The paper deals with information theory and coding, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses compression and communication schemes, which are related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The second part of the paper deals with sparse recovery, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
